      "side": 1,
      "message": "I do like the way SkArenaAlloc branches on std::is_trivially_destructible\u003cT\u003e::value to handle this POD/non-POD distinction for you.  Surely it\u0027s compiling away as if a constexpr-if for different T, right?\n\nI guess the idea here is that you get a different type back?  But why not use a unique_ptr with destroyer in both cases?  The destroyer will no-op out for POD T.",
